{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}} {{Infobox military unit |unit_name=11th U-boat Flotilla |image=[[File:11 Flottille Emblem.png]] |caption=The 11th Flotilla emblem |country=[[Nazi Germany]] |type=[[U-boat]] flotilla |branch=''[[Kriegsmarine]]'' |dates=Raised May, 1942, Dissolved May, 1945 |command_structure= |garrison=[[Bergen|Bergen, Norway]] |nickname= |battles=[[Battle of the Atlantic (1939-1945)]] |notable_commanders=''[[Korvettenkapitän]]'' [[Heinrich Lehmann-Willenbrock]] |associated units= }} The '''11th U-boat Flotilla''' ([[German language|German]] ''11. Unterseebootsflottille'') was formed on 15 May 1942 in [[Bergen|Bergen, Norway]]. The flotilla operated mainly in the [[North Sea]] and against the [[Arctic convoys of World War II|Russian convoys]] (JW-, PQ-, QP- and RA series) in the [[Arctic Sea]]. The flotilla operated various marks of the [[Type VII U-boat]] until September, 1944, when it had an influx of some [[Type IX U-boat|Type IX boats]] from France. It also was the only flotilla to field the [[Type XXI U-boat]] for operational use, but the war ended before {{GS|U-2511||2}} saw action. The Flotilla was disbanded on 9 May 1945 with the German surrender.
